17. Forecast and Prediction Uncertainty
Weather forecasts and predictions provided by AUS Weather are sourced from reputable organizations, namely the Bureau of Meteorology (BOM) and the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA). Despite our efforts to ensure accuracy, weather forecasts are inherently uncertain and may differ between sources. Factors contributing to this uncertainty include but are not limited to: rapidly changing meteorological conditions, geographic variations, and model and technology limitations. Users are advised to use the forecasts as guidance and not as absolute predictions. We recommend cross-referencing with other weather information sources and using personal judgment in decision-making processes influenced by weather conditions.
18. No Guarantee of Accuracy
